                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.24/147: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-03T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >February 3, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Department’s telegram No. 8, January 30, 4 p.m. These and other shipments
                    cartridges of same calibre are for sale by importers to general public for
                    revolvers. The Government of Honduras granted licenses for this and former
                    shipments 32 and 38 calibre in consideration of a reduction of its outstanding
                    debts owed these importers for other merchandise. Most of these cartridges are
                    ultimately smuggled to Salvador and Guatemala.</p>
                <p>If we raise embargo<note n="18" xml:id="d599fn18">See <ref
                            target="frus1924v02#pg_322">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1924, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 322</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1924v02#pg_324">324</ref>.</note> cartridges will be bought
                    in Canada or Europe and I believe advisable continue embargo in order to retain
                    certain check on destination of ammunition especially for rifles.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
